1. Consists of office buildings, except those constructed at manufacturing sites and those
constructed by power utilities for their own use. Includes all financial buildings.  Medical
buildings are included in health care.
2. Includes buildings and structures used by the retail, wholesale and selected service
industries.  Consists of auto dealerships, garages, service stations, drug stores,
restaurants, mobile structures, and other structures used for commercial purposes.  Bus
or truck garages are included in transportation.
3. Consists primarily of railroads.
4. Includes water supply, sewage and waste disposal, public safety, highway and street, and
conservation and development.
5. Excludes net purchases of used structures and brokers' commissions on the sale of structures.
